As a father of 5 girls I’m especially inspired to combat the gender pay gap. Leaders, if you haven’t already, incorporate a few key changes to your business practices:
➡️ Regularly assess earnings by gender
➡️ Promote pay transparency
➡️ Encourage & invest in female entrepreneurs

This exists for several reasons: Until recently there were different levels of educational attainment for men & women. Women choose different occupations than men & salaries vary. Women make up 57% of part-time work, believed to be a result of gender differences in household care

#EqualPayDay symbolizes how far into the year women must work to earn what men earned in the previous year. This pay gap is even greater for women of color. For Latinas, who on average make 55 cents on the dollar compared to white non-Hispanic men, equal pay day is in October.
